article.description: Kedra Holland-Corn scored 20 points and Yolando Griffith added 18 as the Sacramento Monarchs beat the Orlando Miracle 82-72 on Thursday night.
article.headline: Miracle's playoff hopes fading
article.linkText: Monarchs seriously dent Miracle's playoff hopes
article.story:
ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Kedra Holland-Corn scored 20 points and
Yolando Griffith added 18 as the Sacramento Monarchs beat the
Orlando Miracle 82-72 on Thursday night.

	   Wendy Palmer led Orlando with 17 points as the Miracle dropped a
half-game behind Indiana with two games left in the race for the
fourth and final Eastern Conference playoff spot.

	   Fourth-place Indiana, which beat Orlando on Wednesday night, has
three games left and holds the tiebreaker over the Miracle.

	   "I don't think we played a very good transition defense and
that hurt us late,'' Miracle guard Pee Wee Johnson said. "This was
an important game. It's definitely do-or-die now.''

	   Sacramento, which won for the ninth time in eleven games to
improve to 12-17, is out of the Western Conference playoff race.

	   "I'm proud of this team,'' Sacramento coach Maura McHugh said.
"We had something to prove to ourselves. Just because the playoffs
aren't there doesn't mean we don't have something to play for.''

	   Ahead 67-65 with 3:42 to play, the Monarchs broke away with an
8-2 run to make it 75-67 with 49 seconds left. Ticha Penicheiro
scored four points during the run.

	   Griffith also had 10 rebounds for the Monarchs, and Penicheiro
had 11 points and 12 assists. Johnson and Nykesha Sales each scored
16 points for the Miracle.

	   With Orlando's loss, first-place New York and second-place
Washington clinched Eastern Conference playoff spots.
